data.title: Richard Dennis Wynn Obituary 2016

data.text:
Ricky Wynn, 59, of Ledbetter passed away on Monday, November 14, 2016 at his residence.

Mr. Wynn worked as an electrician and in maintenance. He was a member of Friendship United Methodist Church in Lyon County and a United States Navy Veteran. In his free time, he enjoyed spending time outdoors, hunting, fishing, golfing, and watching UK Basketball.

Surviving is his wife, Donna Wynn; one son, Eric Wynn of Ledbetter, KY; his mother, Geraldine Wynn of Smithland, KY; two brothers, Tony Wynn of Benton, KY and Christopher Wynn of Atlanta, GA; one sister, Sherri Allen of Smithland, KY; six nieces; five nephews; one great-niece; and eight great-nephews.

He was preceded in death by his father, Harold Wynn.

Friends may call from 5:00pm to 7:00pm on Thursday at the Smith Funeral Chapel.

Memorial Services will be held at 7:00pm on Thursday, November 17, 2016 at Smith Funeral Chapel with Rev. Joel Jackson officiating.

Memorial contributions may be made to St. Jude Children Hospital at 501 St. Jude Place Memphis, TN 38105.

Online condolences may be left at www.smithfc.com

Smith Funeral Chapel in Smithland is in charge of arrangements.
